{"TopicId":217973,"ForumId":200,"TopicTitle":"Fairings suddenly speed towards kerbin after being jettisoned","CreatedByName":"Joker58th","CreatedById":178441,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T23:32:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Joker58th","CreatedById":178441,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T23:32:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP: 0.1.0.0.20893 | Windows 11 | i7-12700 | RTX 2080\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter deploying a fairing, it falls straight down shortly after deployment.\u00A0 Video below.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/AfmR7uo.mp4\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://i.imgur.com/AfmR7uo.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-09T14:04:17Z\u0022 title=\u002207/09/2023 02:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 9, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Equatis","CreatedById":225649,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-16T23:39:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP Version:\u00A0v0.1.1.0 (Updated on 3/16/203)\u003Cbr\u003E\nOperating System: Windows 11\u003Cbr\u003E\nCPU and GPU: 5800X3D and 7900XTX\u003Cbr\u003E\nDescription of the bug: When I get into orbit and eject my fairings and activate next stage (an engine) my fairings shoot towards Kerbin.\u003Cbr\u003E\nExpected Behavior: Fairing pieces and coupler float freely and should only be affected by propulsion.\u003Cbr\u003E\nObserved Behavior: Fairing pieces and coupler rocket towards Kerbin.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSteps to Replicate: Seems to do it every time for me.\u003Cbr\u003E\nFixes / Workarounds: None I know of.\u003Cbr\u003E\nA list of ALL mods: No mods.\u003Cbr\u003E\nOther Notes / Screenshots / Log Files: YouTube video link is\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/-J5u7VZ-rMQ?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Strange Fairings v0.1.1.0 KSP2\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-16T23:39:26Z\u0022 title=\u002203/16/2023 11:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Equatis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Speeding Mullet","CreatedById":62635,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T11:51:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReplicated in v0.1.1.0, however, was not quick enough to get a screenshot.\u00A0 Report as follows:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EKSP Version -\u00A00.1.1.0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003EOperating System and version \u00A0- Windows 11\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003ECPU and GPU models - Intel core i5 12600KF / NVIDIA GeFroce RTX 3080\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription of the bug. \u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EExpected\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EBehaviour\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0- fairings decouple and drift apart\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EObserved\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003EBehaviour\u003C/b\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0-\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Efairings eject forward through payload, then rapidly descend straight down to Kerbin\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003ESteps to Replicate - Rockket with fairing, eject fairing.\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFixes / Workarounds (if known..) unknown\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA list of ALL mods - None\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOther Notes: None\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESM\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mamboguy12","CreatedById":29935,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-17T11:59:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt also does this in orbit of the Mun.\u00A0 \u00A0Fairings went through lander they were covering when deployed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SeismicSlammer85","CreatedById":226714,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T16:14:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.3 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0windows | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0ryzen 7 | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Nvidia Geforce GTX 1660 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003Eidk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA few seconds after deploying fairings, their physics and trajectory suddenly changes and the fairing shell shoots downwards towards kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, fairings seem to deploy incorrectly, as instead of splitting open, the fairing goes forward in one piece, as if it\u0027s being slid off the rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-24T16:33:25Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2023 04:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T16:45:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/226714-seismicslammer85/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022226714\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/226714-seismicslammer85/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SeismicSlammer85\u003C/a\u003EMerged your bug report into these ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T21:20:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo add to this: Fairings also always go mostly forward for me and don\u0027t really split.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot a new bug for me. Has always been there and it is kind of like a running gag for me now every time I jettison a fairing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-24T21:20:43Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2023 09:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 24, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by running_bird\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Buzz313th","CreatedById":149043,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-24T23:54:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis Bug has been around since the first patch.\u00A0 Before the first patch the fairings used to get stuck on parts of the craft.\u00A0 I\u0027m assuming the fix for getting stuck was to just shoot them at high velocity off the craft..\u00A0 LOL\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-25T00:50:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey can also go up instead of down. I have watched debris in aparabolic curve with an apoapsis over 300 km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}